 This is not an argument regarding the merits of gun control laws.
 The Second Amendment stated one of the subjects about which the federal government was prohibited from making any laws.
 Cruikshank established the view of the U.S.
 The court in Cruikshank said that the Second Amendment did not create a federally protected right of individuals but was an express limitation on the powers of the national (federal) government.
 There have been lower federal court decisions regarding the Second Amendment, all supportive of this established principle.
